The members of “PDP 2019 Edo State House of Assembly Candidates Forum” have congratulated the incumbent governor of Edo state , Governor Obaseki for a well deserved victory at the just concluded Gubernatorial Primary Election of PDP. According to a statement made available to LEADERSHIP, the group who said they are still members of PDP and representing various Constituencies across the Local Governments in the State, are highly fascinated by his well deserved victory. The statement signed by
Hon. (Sir) Ezehi MD. Igbas
Minority Whip EDHA (2015 to 2019)
Esan North East Constituency2. Chairman PDP EDHA Candidates Forum, Nosa Victor Omoregie (Ovia North East 1 Constituency)-Secretary, PDP EDHA Candidates Forum, Zubairu Dada Abubakar (Etsako West 1 Constituency) -Member, Afebu Aigbonoga Esq (Etsako West 2 Constituency) -Member, Jimmy Osagiede Esq (Egor Constituency) -Member, Ekoh Ekoyomo Innocent (Esan Central Constituency) -Member, Ibizugbe Stephen Osayomwanbor (Ovia North East 2 Constituency)- Member, Veadams Ezekiel Ighodaro (Uhunmwonde Constituency)-Member, Hon. Godwin Adenomo (former member EDHA) Ovia South South West Constituency -Member, Lion Okoro Osadebamwen (Oredo East Constituency) – Member
and Eghosa Asemota Aigbonifo (Oredo West Constituency) – Member stated that “Your victory is made in heaven and we sincerely rejoice with you, members of our great party and majority of Edo People for this wonderful feat, hence accept our hearty congratulations. “Let us assure you of our maximum support at ensuring that the September 19, 2020 Governorship Election is prosecuted successfully in favour of you, our candidate and People Democratic Party “PDP” our great party.”